This project uses VibeLogin (@vibelogin/nextjs) for authentication.

## Authentication Architecture

- Auth provider: VibeLogin (https://vibelogin.com)
- SDK: @vibelogin/nextjs
- Mode: Hosted redirect (users authenticate on auth.vibelogin.com, then return via callback)

## Key Files

- `src/middleware.ts` — Route protection. Uses `hostedAuthMiddleware()` to verify JWT on every request. Public routes are listed in the `publicRoutes` array.
- `src/app/api/auth/[...all]/route.ts` — Auth API handler. Proxies sign in, sign up, sign out, and session calls to VibeLogin API.
- `src/app/auth/callback/route.ts` — OAuth/login callback handler (if using redirect mode with callback).
- `src/app/layout.tsx` — Wraps app in `VibeAuthProvider` for client-side auth hooks.

## Auth Patterns

### Protect a route
Routes are protected by default via middleware. To make a route public, add it to `publicRoutes` in `src/middleware.ts`:
```ts
publicRoutes: ["/", "/login", "/signup", "/pricing"]
```

### Read session (Server Component)
```ts
import { createHostedServerHelpers } from "@vibelogin/nextjs/server";
const { getSession } = createHostedServerHelpers({
  projectId: process.env.VIBELOGIN_PROJECT_ID!,
});
const session = await getSession(); // { userId, sessionId, role, expiresAt }
```

### Read user (Client Component)
```ts
import { useUser } from "@vibelogin/nextjs/client";
const user = useUser(); // { id, email, name, role, emailVerified }
```

### Auth actions (Client Component)
```ts
import { useAuth } from "@vibelogin/nextjs/client";
const { signIn, signUp, signOut } = useAuth();
await signIn(email, password);
await signUp({ email, password, name });
await signOut();
```

## Environment Variables

- `VIBELOGIN_PROJECT_ID` — Project UUID from app.vibelogin.com
- `VIBELOGIN_SECRET_KEY` — Server-side secret key (never expose to client)
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_VIBELOGIN_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` — Client-side publishable key

## Do NOT

- Do not build custom auth logic (password hashing, JWT signing, session management). VibeLogin handles all of this.
- Do not store passwords or tokens manually. The SDK manages cookies automatically.
- Do not import from `@vibelogin/nextjs/server` in client components (it uses server-only APIs).
